sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT player_id) 
FROM players 
WHERE team_id = (SELECT team_id FROM players WHERE player_name = 'John Doe');

SELECT SUM(t.stadium_capacity * 5) AS total_investment_in_millions
FROM teams t
JOIN seasons s ON t.team_id = s.champion_team_id;

SELECT AVG(minutes_played) AS typical_duration
FROM player_stats
WHERE goals_scored > 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'Player A' refers to a specific individual in the database;
- 'Team A' is the name of the team the player is associated with;
- The performance metrics give insight into how well the player and team are doing in the league.
